medical_history.chief_complaint: Right lower quadrant (RLQ) pain for 24 hours.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Patient developed acute onset sharp RLQ pain around 8pm while in class, with radiation to right flank and left lower quadrant. Pain was exacerbated by movement and was at its worst described as severe requiring her to "freeze" up. Pain has been constant and unchanged in quality since onset, which is the longest duration she has experienced compared to her previous ovarian cyst pain. Denies any accompanying symptoms such as fevers, chills, nausea, vomiting, or abnormal vaginal bleeding.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Endometriosis on continuous OCP, bilateral ruptured ovarian cysts status post laparoscopic cystectomy, migraine headache, seizure disorder (remote), concussion, anxiety.
